1. Normal saline can be administered.
2. Administration of normal saline might increase circulating levels of pro-inflammatory cytokines.
3. Administration of normal saline may cause variation of plasmatic electrolytic.
4. Administration of normal saline can lead to hyperchloremic acidosis.
5. Hyperchloremic acidosis can impair renal function.

messages.content:
Statement: Administration of normal saline might increase circulating levels of pro-inflammatory cytokines and may cause variation of plasmatic electrolytic and hyperchloremic acidosis, which in turn can impair renal function.
